<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Caesar Salad</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 head romaine lettuce, washed and torn into bite-sized pieces</li>
            <li>1 cup croutons</li>
            <li>1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese</li>
            <li>1/4 cup Caesar dressing</li>
            <li>1 lemon, juiced</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon Dijon mustard</li>
            <li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>Salt and black pepper, to taste</li>
            <li>1/4 cup olive oil</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2> Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>salad</li>
            <li>side dish</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a small bowl, whisk together lemon juice, Dijon mustard, minced garlic, salt, and black pepper.</li>
            <li>While whisking, slowly drizzle in the olive oil until the dressing emulsifies.</li>
            <li>In a large salad bowl, combine the torn romaine lettuce, croutons, and grated Parmesan cheese.</li>
            <li>Drizzle the Caesar dressing over the salad and toss until everything is well coated.</li>
            <li>Serve the Caesar Salad immediately as a refreshing side dish.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious Caesar Salad!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

